</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-28_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Performing CPR involves direct physical contact and often, the exposure to bodily fluids. Ineffective hygiene measures can increase the risk of cross-contamination and transmission of infections, including viral pathogens such as HBV, HCV, and HIV. Statistics from health authorities highlight the significance of adhering to hygiene protocols, with studies indicating that proper sanitation can reduce the risk of infection transmission by up to 80%.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-30_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-31_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-32_ pf-heading-1-h3">Understanding key definitions</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR)</strong> - A lifesaving technique used in emergencies when someone's heartbeat or breathing has stopped.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Hygiene during CPR</strong> - Refers to the practices involved in preventing infection during CPR, including the use of barriers like face masks and gloves.



</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-39_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-40_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-41_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation and regulations</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-43_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">CPR training in the UK is guided by regulations from the Health and Safety Executive (HSE) and recommendations by the Resuscitation Council (UK). These guidelines emphasise the importance of hygiene in CPR to prevent the transmission of infections. Compliance with these regulations is not just best practice—it is a requisite under the Health and Safety at Work etc. Act 1974, which mandates adequate training and measures to ensure the health and safety of both rescuers and victims.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-45_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-46_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-47_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices in hygiene during CPR</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-49_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Use of personal protective equipment (PPE) </strong>- Gloves, masks, and protective eyewear should be worn during training and actual resuscitation attempts.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>Proper disposal of PPE </strong>- After performing CPR, all used PPE should be disposed of safely and hygienically to prevent contamination.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-54_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular sanitisation</strong> - CPR manikins used in training should be cleaned and disinfected after each use, adhering to manufacturers' guidelines and infection control protocols.







</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-56_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-57_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-58_ pf-heading-1-h3">Implementing effective training strategies</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-60_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-61_ pf-text-1"><strong>Incorporate hygiene protocols in CPR training</strong> - Educators should integrate hygiene practices into the CPR curriculum, ensuring that trainees understand their importance and demonstrate proficiency.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-63_ pf-text-1"><strong>Simulation-based learning</strong> - Utilising advanced manikins and simulations to teach correct hygiene techniques can enhance the learning experience and preparedness of healthcare providers.






