</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-69_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Organisations involved in providing CPR training must ensure that their courses are comprehensive, up-to-date, and compliant with current legislation. It is recommended that training programmes are regularly reviewed and updated in line with the latest guidelines from the Resuscitation Council (UK) and HSE. All training materials emphasise the importance of hygiene during CPR. Continuous professional development (CPD) opportunities are provided to keep healthcare providers aware of the latest hygiene practices in CPR.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-71_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-72_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-73_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
